<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="364" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,258,574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,399,258,283]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Description. Female.</emphasis>
Body length (incl. forewing) 16.3 mm, head width 3.6 mm (incl. eyes), pronotum width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="364" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
. Colour as in previous species but brown marking paler (
<figureCitation box="[837,973,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[201,1394,213,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[186,1410,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Elongationa sp. 13, habitus, dorsal view; 14, habitus, lateral view; 15, forewing; 16, face; 17, female first valvulae; 18, magnified view of apex of first valvulae; 19, female second valvulae; 20, magnified view of apex of female second valvulae. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 13 - 16); 0.2 mm (Figs. 18, 20); 0.5 mm (Figs. 17,19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832732/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Figs. 13, 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,258,574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">
Female with 1st and 2nd valvulae narrow, curved dorsally; 1st strigate apically and 2nd elevated medially with one large and three or four small dorsal subapical teeth (
<figureCitation box="[733,954,369,394]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1935,1958]" captionTargetBox="[201,1394,213,1854]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[186,1410,195,1923]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Elongationa sp. 13, habitus, dorsal view; 14, habitus, lateral view; 15, forewing; 16, face; 17, female first valvulae; 18, magnified view of apex of first valvulae; 19, female second valvulae; 20, magnified view of apex of female second valvulae. Scale bars = 1.0 mm (Figs. 13 - 16); 0.2 mm (Figs. 18, 20); 0.5 mm (Figs. 17,19)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/832732/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="364">Figs. 17, 18, 19, 20</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
